history.content: The 'swap' feature was designed to address this. There are no guarantees but you have a good chance of getting into the class.

Hi, if I'm not a CS major and I enroll in the waitlist for CS170 for the spring semester, will I be able to get in? On the course scheduler website it says that there are 328 students already enrolled and there are 302 students on the waitlist right now, but the enrollment limit is 527. I was wondering if it's a good idea or not to drop another one of my classes to get in the waitlist for CS170 before its too late, but I'm afraid that I won't get into the class in the end and will lose my spot in another class as a result.
history.subject: CS170 Waitlist Question
